Additional details

Doors open: 18:00

Tour name: The Mermaid Gang Tour

~ FELLY ~

With nearly 40,000 subscribers on YouTube
and over 12 million listens on SoundCloud, artist/producer Felly has experienced unbelievable growth since his introduction to the hip-hop world only four years ago. The 20 year-old’s music, instrumentals and freestyles have racked up over 7 million views on YouTube in the process, with his most recent project This Shit Comes in Waves, demonstrating maturity surpassing any previous releases. Building off of his last four projects and nine beat-tapes from the past several years, his most recent This Shit Comes in Waves presents the epitome of the unique sound Fel has been developing for the past several years.

~ GYYPS ~

Gyyps is a rapper, producer and songwriter from the Los Angeles area. In 2015, Gyyps took his career into his own hands and released both his debut Canoga Park EP and Darryl Mixtape, amassing over 3 million total Soundlcloud listens in only 9 months.

~ SONGSBYH ~

Born in a small town in Northern Michigan, hip-hop artist/producer/engineer songsbyh (or simply H) orginially moved to Colorado as a competitive skier. It wasn't until his participation at the Dew Tour though that his dreams came to a head when he realized that he was more passionate about the music reverberating in his ears than the slopes he was gazing down upon.
​
Now with headlining shows and festival slots under his belt, songsbyh has gained a dedicated following who have passionately accompanied him on his swift rise as he has shared the stage with acts including Tory Lanez, Kid Ink, KYLE, and Mick Jenkins.
